    "# Observations about Gun Deaths in the US\n",
    "### A report on what I have learned so far and what I think may need to be observed further.\n",
    "\n",
    "After extracting the file `guns.csv` I went on to create dictionaries that were categorized by:\n",
    "\n",
    "- Date of crime\n",
    "\n",
    "- Race \n",
    "\n",
    "- Sex\n",
    "\n",
    "**What** I have noticed so far, is nothing far from what I would have expected. \n",
    "\n",
    "In terms of sex, males are the predominant sex for gun deaths. For race, Whites followed by Blacks are the highest amount of deaths. If anything, I would say what is interesting is that blacks represent about 12% of the US population yet **as far as gun deaths go, they are roughly the victims of one in four gun deaths in the US.** Something that also surprised me, was the trends over the years. The fact of the matter is that the amounts of gun deaths per year has changed very little over the last few years despite all the fear pushed out over news outlets with mass shooters. Althought the topic of mass shooting is an issue that I would not want to discuss here in this observation."
